      "message": "[minor] Line 23: 🟡 Suggestion: Consider grouping both Windows-specific `#undef` blocks under a single `#ifdef _WIN32` / `#endif` guard. This makes it explicit that these workarounds are Windows-only and avoids unnecessary preprocessor checks on other platforms. However, the current approach (guarded `#ifdef MACRO` / `#undef`) is safe and already idiomatic in this file, so this is a minor style suggestion.\n\n```suggestion\n#ifdef _WIN32\n// Defined in windows.h\n#ifdef ERROR\n#undef ERROR\n#endif\n// Defined in nb30.h (Windows NetBIOS header)\n#ifdef REGISTERED\n#undef REGISTERED\n#endif\n#endif // _WIN32\n```",
